{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":107875,"duration_api_ms":212875,"num_turns":6,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"27dce0ef-0517-4588-91a5-850b7d74c156","total_cost_usd":0.5458844999999999,"usage":{"input_tokens":964,"cache_creation_input_tokens":27280,"cache_read_input_tokens":79242,"output_tokens":2651,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":27280,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":253,"outputTokens":12601,"cacheReadInputTokens":991980,"cacheCreationInputTokens":81770,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.2646685000000001,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000},"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":964,"outputTokens":2651,"cacheReadInputTokens":79242,"cacheCreationInputTokens":27280,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.281216,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"summary":"All four amendments are verified as accurate against the source code. Two are correctness bugs (duplicate journal events, Paused clobber), one is a confirmed redundancy with misleading semantics, and one is a reasonable test maintainability improvement. I accept all four.","votes":[{"amendment_id":"fr-8-841107a4","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified: `current_bead_runs` at service.rs:169 is already the output of `latest_task_runs_per_bead`, and `active_bead_ids` (model.rs:368-374) calls `latest_task_runs_per_bead` again internally. The second deduplication pass is provably a no-op. Beyond the wasted O(n) work, the call to `active_bead_ids` on already-collapsed data is misleading — it implies the input hasn't been deduplicated yet. Replacing with a direct filter eliminates both the redundancy and the false signal."},{"amendment_id":"fr-8-7e4d3238","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified: `Mutex<Option<T>>::take()` on both `attempted_tx` and `proceed_rx` (service.rs:754-762) means the first `with_milestone_write_lock` call consumes both channels, and subsequent calls silently skip signaling. The type implements the full `MilestoneSnapshotPort` trait, so nothing in its interface signals single-use semantics. Adding a comment or debug assertion is a low-cost improvement that prevents a future test author from reusing the store and getting silently broken coordination."},{"amendment_id":"fr-8-beaac5f9","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified as a real idempotency bug. The chain is clear: (1) `completion_event_details` (service.rs:233-245) includes optional `plan_hash` and `outcome_detail` in the details string; (2) `append_event_if_missing` (fs.rs:2335-2341) deduplicates on exact `details` equality; (3) `backfill_terminal_entry` (fs.rs:2425-2457) fills in missing optional fields on replay without conflict; (4) the enriched entry produces a different details string, bypassing deduplication. Result: the same logical completion gets two journal entries. The fix should either exclude backfill-only fields from the dedup key or update the existing event in place."},{"amendment_id":"fr-8-3e84cce1","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified as a real state-corruption bug. `reconcile_snapshot_from_lineage` (service.rs:213-216) rewrites any non-terminal status to `Ready` when task runs exist, and `is_terminal` (model.rs:78-80) only covers Completed/Abandoned — so `Paused` is treated identically to Active. Since `update_task_run` (service.rs:574-583) calls reconciliation and persists the result on every completion or backfill, any bead finishing on a paused milestone silently clears the operator-imposed pause. The fix should preserve Paused by checking for it explicitly before overwriting."}]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"320951bc-208a-4366-b0a5-fa3e74eb3ef2"}
